defs.docs:
Implementation of [yamux](https://github.com/hashicorp/yamux/blob/master/spec.md), a multiplexer
 over reliable, ordered connections, such as TCP/IP.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (res: T, cfg: Config, mode: Mode) -> Self

defs.name: open_stream
defs.docs: Open a new outbound stream which is multiplexed over the existing connection.

defs.name: StreamHandle
defs.docs: A handle to a multiplexed stream.

defs.name: credit
defs.docs: Report how much sending credit this stream has available.

defs.name: ConnectionError
defs.value: ConnectionError::{Io, Decode, NoMoreStreamIds, Closed, StreamNotFound, TooManyStreams, TooManyPendingFrames, __Nonexhaustive}

defs.name: OnReceive
defs.docs: Send window updates as soon as a stream's receive window drops to 0.

defs.name: OnRead
defs.docs: Send window updates only when data is read on the receiving end.

defs.name: WindowUpdateMode
defs.docs: Specifies when window update frames are sent.

defs.name: set_receive_window
defs.docs: Set the receive window (must be >= 256 KiB).

defs.name: set_max_buffer_size
defs.docs: Set the max. buffer size per stream.

defs.name: set_max_num_streams
defs.docs: Set the max. number of streams.

defs.name: set_max_pending_frames
defs.docs:
Set the max. number of pending frames, i.e. outgoing
 frames which have not yet been sent.

defs.name: set_window_update_mode
defs.docs: Set the window update mode to use.

defs.name: set_read_after_close
defs.docs:
Allow or disallow streams to read from buffered data after
 the connection has been closed.
